<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Flout2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Flout,</orth> vb. to mock, to make a fool of; 1) trans.: <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 130</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.327" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 327</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.373" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 373</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 2, 49</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. with <emph>at</emph>: <cit><quote>never f. at me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 4, 108</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.246" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 246</bibl>. Absolutely: <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 1, 13</bibl>. With an accus. denoting the result: <cit><quote>a college of wit-crackers cannot f. me out of my humour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 4, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>f. me out of my calling,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 108</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ere you f. old ends any further,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.290" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 290</bibl></cit> (i. e. recite old ends to mock me).
